==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Boatman
<hw>Boat"man</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Boatmen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A man who
manages a boat; a rower of a boat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As late the <qex>boatman</qex> hies him home.</q>
<rj><qau>Percival.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A boat bug. See <er>Boat
bug</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boatmanship</ent>⟦br⟧
